  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  One or more sBCC on torso, neck or face

          -  Total surface area &lt;= 40 sq cm

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Pregnancy or women who are breastfeeding

          -  Xeroderma pigmentosum, albinism, epidermodysplasia verruciformis, any genetic anomaly
             accompanied by skin tumors

          -  Metatypical, adnexal, or sclerodermiform carcinomas

          -  Current or other previous malignant skin tumor (epidermoid carcinoma, melanoma) in the
             region of the current lesion

          -  Known HIV positive serology

          -  Skin tumor that is already or highly likely to become metastatic

          -  Presence of a clinically significant anomaly or illness (immunological,
             cardiovascular, pulmonary, hematological, neurological, hepatic, renal, endocrine,
             gastrointestinal, collagenous)

          -  Previous organ transplant history
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
